Description: Defuse <stdbool.h> for PG10 char-bool to avoid gcc 13 type conflicts
 PG10 typedef'd `bool` as `char`. Modern glibc/libc++ system headers
 (immintrin.h, etc.) transitively include <stdbool.h>, which
 `#define bool _Bool`. When that happens partway through a TU, header
 decls and definitions disagree (one sees char, one sees _Bool), causing
 "conflicting types" errors with gcc 13/14.
 .
 Pre-define _STDBOOL_H BEFORE the first system header so subsequent
 #include <stdbool.h> becomes a no-op TU-wide.
Author: OpenTenBase Packaging <packaging@opentenbase.org>
Forwarded: not-needed
Last-Update: 2026-05-17

--- a/src/include/c.h
+++ b/src/include/c.h
@@ -45,6 +45,16 @@
 #ifndef C_H
 #define C_H

+/*
+ * Pre-define gcc's <stdbool.h> include guard so it becomes a no-op for the
+ * remainder of the translation unit. PG10 uses `typedef char bool` (sizeof=1,
+ * baked into on-disk format); we must not let stdbool.h's
+ * `#define bool _Bool` race with our typedef mid-TU via transitive includes
+ * from system headers like immintrin.h.
+ */
+#define _STDBOOL_H 1
+#define __bool_true_false_are_defined 1
+
 #if defined(__x86_64__)
 #include "immintrin.h"
 #endif
